The paper proposes an algorithm for finding longest repetitive substrings in strings, which is a problem in the field of string algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The algorithm also has time and space complexity considerations, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the problem of repeat finding has applications in computational biology, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
